universe of origin : the between — the domain that belongs to neither side
seal               : Push a system too far toward order and it freezes, rigid and dead. Push it toward randomness and it dissolves into noise. But on the narrow boundary between — the edge of chaos — something remarkable happens: structure stable enough to persist and fluid enough to change. Complexity scientists suspect this is where computation, life, and perhaps mind itself prefer to live.
